8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to S.P. 401,
9 L.D. 911, “An Act to Modify Ranked-choice Voting with Regard to Candidates Who
10 Withdraw from an Election”
11 Amend the amendment by inserting before section 1 the following:
12 'Sec. 1. 21-A MRSA §1, sub-§27-C, as repealed and replaced by PL 2021, c. 273,
13 §1, is amended by enacting at the end a new first blocked paragraph to read:
14 If one or more of the candidates who have qualified to be listed on the ballot for a particular
15 office in an election determined by ranked-choice voting die, are disqualified or withdraw
16 less than 70 days before the election, the election remains an election determined by
17 ranked-choice voting regardless of the number of remaining candidates.'
18 Amend the amendment in section 1 in subsection 5 in the 14th to 18th lines (page 1,
19 lines 32 to 36 in amendment) by striking out the following: "Notwithstanding the provision
20 of section 1, subsection 27-C that describes the minimum number of qualified candidates
21 for an election to be an election determined by ranked-choice voting, if a candidate dies or
22 becomes disqualified less than 70 days before the primary election, the election remains an
23 election determined by ranked-choice voting regardless of the number of remaining
24 qualified candidates. A" and inserting the following: 'In an election determined by ranked-
25 choice voting, a'
26 Amend the amendment in section 2 in subsection 6 in the 12th to 16th lines (page 2,
27 lines 18 to 22 in amendment) by striking out the following: "Notwithstanding the provision
28 of section 1, subsection 27-C that describes the minimum number of qualified candidates
29 for an election to be an election determined by ranked-choice voting, if a candidate
30 withdraws less than 70 days before the primary election, the election remains an election
31 determined by ranked-choice voting regardless of the number of remaining qualified
32 candidates. A" and inserting the following: 'In an election determined by ranked-choice
33 voting, a'
34 Amend the amendment in section 3 in subsection 3 in paragraph C in the 12th to 16th
35 lines (page 3, lines 6 to 10 in amendment) by striking out the following: "Notwithstanding
36 the provision of section 1, subsection 27-C that describes the minimum number of qualified
37 candidates for an election to be an election determined by ranked-choice voting, if a
38 candidate withdraws pursuant to this paragraph, the election remains an election
