4 Amend the amendment by inserting after section 3 the following:
5 'Sec. 4. 21-A MRSA §723-A, sub-§1, ¶C, as amended by PL 2023, c. 628, §1, is
6 further amended to read:
7 C. "Continuing candidate" means a candidate who has not been removed from
8 consideration and is not an excluded candidate.
9 Sec. 5. 21-A MRSA §723-A, sub-§1, ¶C-1 is enacted to read:
10 C-1. "Excluded candidate" means a candidate who is listed on the ballot or has
11 qualified as a declared write-in candidate, but has died, been disqualified or withdrawn
12 less than 70 days before the election.
13 Sec. 6. 21-A MRSA §723-A, sub-§2, as amended by PL 2023, c. 628, §2, is further
14 amended to read:
15 2. Procedures. Except as provided in subsections 2-A, 3, 4 and 7, the following
16 procedures are used to determine the winner of an election determined by ranked-choice
17 voting. The If a candidate has been assigned ranking number one on more than 50% of all
18 ballots cast for the particular office for which the candidate is running, including but not
19 limited to ballots on which ranking number one is blank, on which there is an overvote at
20 ranking number one or on which ranking number one was assigned to an excluded
21 candidate, that candidate is declared the winner of the election. If no candidate has been
22 assigned ranking number one on more than 50% of the ballots cast for that particular office,
23 the ranked‑choice voting count must proceed in rounds. In each round, the number of votes
24 for each continuing candidate must be counted. Each continuing ballot counts as one vote
25 for its highest-ranked continuing candidate for that round. Exhausted ballots are not
26 counted for any continuing candidate. The round then ends with one of the following 2
27 potential outcomes.
28 A. If there are 2 or fewer continuing candidates, the candidate with the most votes is
29 declared the winner of the election.
30 B. If there are more than 2 continuing candidates, the last-place candidate is removed
31 from consideration and a new round begins.
32 Sec. 7. 21-A MRSA §723-A, sub-§2-A is enacted to read:
33 2-A. Excluded candidates. In any round of the ranked-choice voting count, a ballot
34 on which an excluded candidate is the highest-ranked candidate must be counted for the
35 next-highest-ranked continuing candidate.'
36 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
37 section number to read consecutively.
